OL,6,FOpening Mrs Jefferies' inquest, he
OL,7,Fsaid: "I'm mandated to continue the
OL,8,Finvestigation into the circumstances
OL,9,Faround Mrs Jefferies' death and
OL,10,Fconclude that by way of inquest.
OL,12,F"Whilst those matters are progressing
OL,13,Fit remains for me to pass on my
OL,14,Fcondolences to Mrs Jefferies' family."
OL,16,FMr Hughes described the situation
OL,17,Fregarding Mr Jefferies as "similar"
OL,18,Fand reiterated his condolences to the
OL,19,Ffamily.
